  "root_text": {
    "an3.122:0.1": "Aṅguttara Nikāya 3.122 ",
    "an3.122:0.2": "12. Āpāyikavagga ",
    "an3.122:0.3": "Moneyyasutta ",
    "an3.122:1.1": "“Tīṇimāni, bhikkhave, moneyyāni. ",
    "an3.122:1.2": "Katamāni tīṇi? ",
    "an3.122:1.3": "Kāyamoneyyaṁ, vacīmoneyyaṁ, manomoneyyaṁ. ",
    "an3.122:1.4": "Katamañca, bhikkhave, kāyamoneyyaṁ? ",
    "an3.122:1.5": "Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu pāṇātipātā paṭivirato hoti, adinnādānā paṭivirato hoti, abrahmacariyā paṭivirato hoti. ",
    "an3.122:1.6": "Idaṁ vuccati, bhikkhave, kāyamoneyyaṁ. ",
    "an3.122:2.1": "Katamañca, bhikkhave, vacīmoneyyaṁ? ",
    "an3.122:2.2": "Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu musāvādā paṭivirato hoti, pisuṇāya vācāya paṭivirato hoti, pharusāya vācāya paṭivirato hoti, samphappalāpā paṭivirato hoti. ",
    "an3.122:2.3": "Idaṁ vuccati, bhikkhave, vacīmoneyyaṁ. ",
    "an3.122:3.1": "Katamañca, bhikkhave, manomoneyyaṁ? ",
    "an3.122:3.2": "Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu āsavānaṁ khayā anāsavaṁ cetovimuttiṁ paññāvimuttiṁ diṭṭheva dhamme sayaṁ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja viharati. ",
    "an3.122:3.3": "Idaṁ vuccati, bhikkhave, manomoneyyaṁ. ",
    "an3.122:3.4": "Imāni kho, bhikkhave, tīṇi moneyyānīti. ",
    "an3.122:4.1": "Kāyamuniṁ vacīmuniṁ, ",
    "an3.122:4.2": "cetomuniṁ anāsavaṁ; ",
    "an3.122:4.3": "Muniṁ moneyyasampannaṁ, ",
    "an3.122:4.4": "āhu sabbappahāyinan”ti. ",
    "an3.122:4.5": "Dasamaṁ. ",
    "an3.122:4.6": "Āpāyikavaggo dutiyo. ",
    "an3.122:5.0": "Tassuddānaṁ ",
    "an3.122:5.1": "Āpāyiko dullabho appameyyaṁ, ",
    "an3.122:5.2": "Āneñjavipattisampadā; ",
    "an3.122:5.3": "Apaṇṇako ca kammanto, ",
    "an3.122:5.4": "Dve soceyyāni moneyyanti. "
  },
  "translation_text": {
    "an3.122:0.1": "Numbered Discourses 3.122 ",
    "an3.122:0.2": "12. Bound for Loss ",
    "an3.122:0.3": "Sagacity ",
    "an3.122:1.1": "“Mendicants, there are these three kinds of sagacity. ",
    "an3.122:1.2": "What three? ",
    "an3.122:1.3": "Sagacity of body, speech, and mind. ",
    "an3.122:1.4": "And what is sagacity of body? ",
    "an3.122:1.5": "It’s when a mendicant doesn’t kill living creatures, steal, or have sex. ",
    "an3.122:1.6": "This is called ‘sagacity of body’. ",
    "an3.122:2.1": "And what is sagacity of speech? ",
    "an3.122:2.2": "It’s when a mendicant doesn’t use speech that’s false, divisive, harsh, or nonsensical. ",
    "an3.122:2.3": "This is called ‘sagacity of speech’. ",
    "an3.122:3.1": "And what is sagacity of mind? ",
    "an3.122:3.2": "It’s when a mendicant realizes the undefiled freedom of heart and freedom by wisdom in this very life. And they live having realized it with their own insight due to the ending of defilements. ",
    "an3.122:3.3": "This is called ‘sagacity of mind’. ",
    "an3.122:3.4": "These are the three kinds of sagacity. ",
    "an3.122:4.1": "A sage in body, a sage in speech, ",
    "an3.122:4.2": "a sage undefiled in heart; ",
    "an3.122:4.3": "a sage, blessed with sagacity, ",
    "an3.122:4.4": "has given up everything, they say.” ",
